#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:2
#: 3b2411c670634a01ae54b817969cfdb3
msgid "混音系统"
msgstr "Mixing System"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:4
#: 628dd517f5024ee88cd9efeb85b5c1ab
msgid "本章讲的是“声音最后从哪里出来、怎样一起调音量、怎样一起加效果”。"
msgstr "This chapter explains where sound is routed, how to adjust groups of sounds together, and how to apply effects to them."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:6
#: 316bc2e9ae974b3bac18561a96f092ef
msgid ""
"如果你刚开始使用 Godot-FmodPlayer，可以先把 :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` 理解成 Godot 的音频总线：音乐走 ``Music``，音效走 ``SFX``，对白走 ``Voice``。把声音分到不同总线后，就可以一次性控制一整类声音。"
msgstr ""
"If you are new to Godot-FmodPlayer, think of a :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` like a Godot audio bus: music goes to ``Music``, sound effects go to ``SFX``, and dialogue goes to ``Voice``. Once sounds are separated into buses, you can control an entire category at once."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:9
#: cafdcfe0d62c4c92a2e1323f41366ea4
msgid "什么时候需要混音系统"
msgstr "When is a mixing system needed"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:11
#: ffdc6e1e1faa4baa815243351ee7df7c
msgid "常见需求可以这样对应："
msgstr "Common needs map to these approaches:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:16
#: 73e54377febd495eb92b75688e192d5f
msgid "你想做的事"
msgstr "What you want to do"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:17
#: 05709ff5de9c4d46befb44c1885ff351
msgid "推荐做法"
msgstr "Recommended approach"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:18
#: d1adabb464414935914c5d51d1c2316f
msgid "调低所有音乐"
msgstr "Lower all music"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:19
#: 50a0774e02d646d78c54c811e81d3258
msgid "把音乐播放到 ``Music`` 总线，然后调这个总线的 ``volume_db``"
msgstr "Play music through the ``Music`` bus, then adjust that bus's ``volume_db``."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:20
#: c3d328516e054de7b3b20980ca54ea2c
msgid "暂停时让音效静音"
msgstr "Mute sound effects while paused"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:21
#: 4e8cd2f414d841eab7d5ecf728f0f5f6
msgid "静音 ``SFX`` 总线"
msgstr "Mute the ``SFX`` bus."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:22
#: 4f598a64806c4a30ae0499b895a83946
msgid "对所有脚步声加滤波"
msgstr "Apply filtering to all footsteps"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:23
#: 466ea977f1dd4908877fcbd9ffb9ed55
msgid "建一个 ``Footsteps`` 总线，并把效果加到这个总线上"
msgstr "Create a ``Footsteps`` bus and add the effect to that bus."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:24
#: 0149c4e035324c76972887b2ba2d64de
msgid "对单个正在播放的声音微调"
msgstr "Fine-tune a single currently playing sound"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:25
#: 0fae5bdf92e8405da33e2f081db3c4af
msgid "取得 :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>`，只控制这一次播放"
msgstr "Get the :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` and control only that playback instance."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:26
#: ebc5957594c142ccb2085b838be94de0
msgid "对一组声音统一控制"
msgstr "Control a group of sounds together"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:27
#: 86da5c856aba40cba10fb33802ed45e9
msgid "使用 :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` 或它底层的 :ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>`"
msgstr "Use a :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` or its underlying :ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>`."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:30
#: 3147126a3c704161af0b8d8f730dcc22
msgid "核心概念"
msgstr "Core Concepts"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:33
#: 0dd4b66619044d32b7a007cd08b0dcc1
msgid "Bus"
msgstr "Bus"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:35
#: c0a1e27a55ab4a4188ad8f066298d4ba
msgid ":ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` 是一条混音路径。你可以把它想成一条“声音分类管道”。"
msgstr "A :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>` is a mixing route. You can think of it as a pipeline for a category of sounds."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:37
#: cdda51c2eb974cdea8f25a7be0c41ca1
msgid "例如："
msgstr "For example:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:39
#: fa1db5f988134b0ab2e9d7abeda44d80
msgid ""
"Master\n"
"├── Music\n"
"├── SFX\n"
"├── Voice\n"
"└── Ambient"
msgstr ""
"Master\n"
"├── Music\n"
"├── SFX\n"
"├── Voice\n"
"└── Ambient"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:47
#: cb90da2c35164f08bab2cd2dd6bae968
msgid "所有声音最后都会汇入 ``Master``。如果把背景音乐送到 ``Music``，把按钮音效送到 ``SFX``，以后就可以分别控制它们。"
msgstr ""
"All sounds eventually flow into ``Master``. If background music goes to ``Music`` and button sounds go to ``SFX``, you can control them separately later."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:50
#: ad17fe187c4248e5b1dc1755803a01d8
msgid "ChannelGroup"
msgstr "ChannelGroup"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:52
#: f076ec7994984466997448e13fa79926
msgid ""
":ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>` 是 FMOD 底层用于混合一组 :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` 的对象。普通使用时优先操作 :ref:`FmodAudioBus<FmodAudioBus>` 或总线布局；只有需要更底层的播放控制时，才直接拿 :ref:`FmodChannelGroup<FmodChannelGroup>`。"
msgstr ""
"A :ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>` is the lower-level FMOD object used to mix a group of :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` objects. For normal use, prefer :ref:`FmodAudioBus<FmodAudioBus>` or the bus layout; access :ref:`FmodChannelGroup<FmodChannelGroup>` directly only when you need lower-level playback control."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:55
#: 8e2bea35f960453e82f6b2caa1fe1148
msgid "DSP"
msgstr "DSP"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:57
#: 86a67b1d35bb4db38442bb3102ab6045
msgid ":ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` 是音频效果处理单元。混响、滤波、延迟、压缩、频谱分析都属于 DSP。多个声音要共享同一个效果时，通常把效果加到总线上，而不是给每个声音单独加。"
msgstr ""
"A :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` is an audio effect processing unit. Reverb, filtering, delay, compression, and spectrum analysis are all DSPs. When multiple sounds should share the same effect, usually add the effect to a bus instead of adding it to every sound individually."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:60
#: b78020326825434b8a40dfadf0a78891
msgid "把声音送到总线"
msgstr "Send Audio to a Bus"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:62
#: a8fdd5436fe34428879752f2b21d0c50
msgid "最简单的方式是设置播放节点的 ``bus``："
msgstr "The simplest way is to set the playback node's ``bus``:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:64
#: 51ca5664c2b94bd2bd3ea8338c04310b
msgid ""
"extends Node\n"
"\n"
"@onready var music := $MusicPlayer\n"
"@onready var hit_sfx := $HitPlayer\n"
"\n"
"func _ready():\n"
"    music.bus = \"Music\"\n"
"    hit_sfx.bus = \"SFX\"\n"
"\n"
"func play_music():\n"
"    music.play()\n"
"\n"
"func play_hit():\n"
"    hit_sfx.play()"
msgstr ""
"extends Node\n"
"\n"
"@onready var music := $MusicPlayer\n"
"@onready var hit_sfx := $HitPlayer\n"
"\n"
"func _ready():\n"
"    music.bus = \"Music\"\n"
"    hit_sfx.bus = \"SFX\"\n"
"\n"
"func play_music():\n"
"    music.play()\n"
"\n"
"func play_hit():\n"
"    hit_sfx.play()"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:81
#: 7c585cf0526941d9b920a3b54eb5266a
msgid "如果你直接用代码播放 :ref:`Sound<glossary-sound>`，就把目标 :ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>` 传给 ``play_sound()``："
msgstr ""
"If you play a :ref:`Sound<glossary-sound>` directly from code, pass the target :ref:`ChannelGroup<glossary-channelgroup>` to ``play_sound()``:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:83
#: 11b3ee6387f84c1aa54ae372e7920529
msgid ""
"func play_ui_sound(path: String):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var ui_bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"UI\")\n"
"    var sound := system.create_sound_from_file(path)\n"
"    return system.play_sound(sound, ui_bus, false)"
msgstr ""
"func play_ui_sound(path: String):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var ui_bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"UI\")\n"
"    var sound := system.create_sound_from_file(path)\n"
"    return system.play_sound(sound, ui_bus, false)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:92
#: c3c5457cd20c42eb93cc4cf0143913f3
msgid "控制总线音量、静音和独奏"
msgstr "Control Bus Volume, Mute, and Solo"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:94
#: e04fb5849ed4418480256d68a68ca2c4
msgid "音量通常用分贝（dB）表示："
msgstr "Volume is usually expressed in decibels (dB):"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:96
#: 7b2428bc26fe41548cfad95a95b904f9
msgid "``0.0`` 表示原始音量。"
msgstr "``0.0`` means the original volume."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:97
#: dcbf0f8a1aa7447d9c2b52d2aa6c27fb
msgid "负数表示变小，例如 ``-6.0``。"
msgstr "Negative values make it quieter, such as ``-6.0``."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:98
#: a4b33388d8f246539754ef28037013db
msgid "正数表示变大，但要小心失真。"
msgstr "Positive values make it louder, but be careful about distortion."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:100
#: 772ceb66308c498aa1caeabf413b8ce9
msgid ""
"func set_music_quiet():\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var music := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Music\")\n"
"\n"
"    music.volume_db = -12.0\n"
"\n"
"func mute_sfx(muted: bool):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var sfx := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"SFX\")\n"
"\n"
"    sfx.mute = muted\n"
"\n"
"func solo_voice(enabled: bool):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var voice := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Voice\")\n"
"\n"
"    voice.solo = enabled"
msgstr ""
"func set_music_quiet():\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var music := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Music\")\n"
"\n"
"    music.volume_db = -12.0\n"
"\n"
"func mute_sfx(muted: bool):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var sfx := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"SFX\")\n"
"\n"
"    sfx.mute = muted\n"
"\n"
"func solo_voice(enabled: bool):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var voice := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Voice\")\n"
"\n"
"    voice.solo = enabled"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:120
#: 61d805210e934d2690c05a790ba79c4b
msgid "``mute`` 是让这条总线静音。``solo`` 是只听这条总线，常用于调试对白、环境声或音乐。"
msgstr ""
"``mute`` silences this bus. ``solo`` lets you hear only this bus, which is useful when debugging dialogue, ambience, or music."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:123
#: 35e88f3add534b76ac3685d73b4305da
msgid "和 Godot 音频总线同步"
msgstr "Synchronize with Godot Audio Buses"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:125
#: 1460aff5c4d5450b971fc987a5fde7cd
msgid ""
"Godot-FmodPlayer 的 FMOD 总线布局会和 Godot 的 `AudioServer`_ 总线布局同步。也就是说，你在 Godot 的音频总线面板里创建的 ``Music``、``SFX``、``Voice`` 等总线，也可以被映射到 FMOD 侧使用。"
msgstr ""
"Godot-FmodPlayer can synchronize the FMOD bus layout with Godot's `AudioServer`_ bus layout. This means buses such as ``Music``, ``SFX``, and ``Voice`` created in Godot's audio bus panel can also be mapped to the FMOD side."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:127
#: 18ab3f59d0ce4f27972be35675ff6329
msgid "通常情况下，你只需要通过 :ref:`FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()<FmodServer-get_audio_bus_layout>` 取得当前布局："
msgstr ""
"Usually, you only need to get the current layout through :ref:`FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()<FmodServer-get_audio_bus_layout>`:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:129
#: e15d2d09270241e781de7ec300f455dd
msgid ""
"func get_layout():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"    return layout"
msgstr ""
"func get_layout():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"    return layout"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:135
#: 756af04d453f43b492f380d02fdca482
msgid "如果你在运行时修改了 Godot 的音频总线结构，可以让 FMOD 侧按需同步："
msgstr "If you modify Godot's audio bus structure at runtime, you can synchronize the FMOD side when needed:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:137
#: 8c75bf5d41294d4eb6a4375a652af8dd
msgid ""
"func sync_buses_from_godot():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"    layout.sync_from_audio_server_if_changed()"
msgstr ""
"func sync_buses_from_godot():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"    layout.sync_from_audio_server_if_changed()"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:143
#: d68e95037d0540b18319c910e29f1c4d
msgid "同步会保留或创建 ``Master`` 总线，并根据 Godot 当前的总线结构更新 FMOD 侧的总线、父子关系、音量、静音、独奏、旁路状态和支持的音频效果。"
msgstr ""
"Synchronization keeps or creates the ``Master`` bus, then updates FMOD-side buses, parent-child relationships, volume, mute, solo, bypass state, and supported audio effects according to Godot's current bus structure."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:147
#: 6be29626e03a47e8b055d2379ba13290
msgid ""
"如果项目的总线结构主要在 Godot 编辑器里维护，推荐优先通过 Godot 音频总线面板创建总线，再让 FMOD 布局同步。只有运行时需要临时总线，或者你明确希望由代码管理总线结构时，再手动调用 ``create_audio_bus()``。"
msgstr ""
"If your project's bus structure is mainly maintained in the Godot editor, prefer creating buses in Godot's audio bus panel and then synchronizing the FMOD layout. Call ``create_audio_bus()`` manually only when you need temporary buses at runtime or explicitly want code to manage the bus structure."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:150
#: e1a05db305384b9f90c5d9abdf1ce8df
msgid "创建自己的总线"
msgstr "Create Your Own Buses"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:152
#: 452b11c383f549b5a19ccdc564a610d1
msgid "默认总线不够用时，可以通过 Godot 音频总线面板新增总线，然后同步到 FMOD。也可以直接通过 :ref:`FmodAudioBusLayout<FmodAudioBusLayout>` 在代码中创建新总线："
msgstr ""
"When the default buses are not enough, you can add buses in Godot's audio bus panel and synchronize them to FMOD. You can also create new buses directly in code through :ref:`FmodAudioBusLayout<FmodAudioBusLayout>`:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:154
#: 4d8429a816ed4e15b75bc686f7a709f6
msgid ""
"func setup_extra_buses():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"UI\", \"Master\")\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"Weapons\", \"SFX\")\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"Footsteps\", \"SFX\")"
msgstr ""
"func setup_extra_buses():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"UI\", \"Master\")\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"Weapons\", \"SFX\")\n"
"    layout.create_audio_bus(\"Footsteps\", \"SFX\")"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:163
#: 70353aeae7224dbd93280dcbd0dc17ab
msgid "建议总线层级先保持简单："
msgstr "Keep the bus hierarchy simple at first:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:165
#: 8fe3c4c36d3744b8b50d110cbbea15ca
msgid ""
"Master\n"
"├── Music\n"
"├── SFX\n"
"│   ├── Weapons\n"
"│   └── Footsteps\n"
"├── Voice\n"
"└── UI"
msgstr ""
"Master\n"
"├── Music\n"
"├── SFX\n"
"│   ├── Weapons\n"
"│   └── Footsteps\n"
"├── Voice\n"
"└── UI"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:175
#: 5973bd88411d418ea62ba1eb6c744c9f
msgid "如果不确定是否要新建总线，先问自己一句：以后是否要单独调它的音量、静音或效果？如果答案是“是”，就适合拆成总线。"
msgstr ""
"If you are not sure whether to create a new bus, ask: will I need to control its volume, mute state, or effects separately later? If the answer is yes, it is a good candidate for its own bus."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:178
#: bebfbe2ade064f6182d20ec882ab0aba
msgid "给总线添加效果"
msgstr "Add Effects to a Bus"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:180
#: 297f3358f6e74316bf206fd3fb1f3c40
msgid "总线效果适合处理“一整类声音”。例如所有室内脚步声都变闷，或者暂停菜单打开时让音乐带一点低通。"
msgstr ""
"Bus effects are useful for processing an entire category of sounds, such as making all indoor footsteps muffled or adding a low-pass effect to music when the pause menu opens."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:182
#: 84eb17f33848425d8e72a8c39b4f1b72
msgid ""
"func add_pause_filter():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"\n"
"    var filter := FmodAudioEffectFilter.new()\n"
"    filter.cutoff_hz = 1200.0\n"
"    filter.resonance = 0.2\n"
"\n"
"    layout.add_bus_effect(\"Music\", filter)"
msgstr ""
"func add_pause_filter():\n"
"    var layout := FmodServer.get_audio_bus_layout()\n"
"\n"
"    var filter := FmodAudioEffectFilter.new()\n"
"    filter.cutoff_hz = 1200.0\n"
"    filter.resonance = 0.2\n"
"\n"
"    layout.add_bus_effect(\"Music\", filter)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:193
#: 88080b85b8a54d34baafabdfbf8ecea1
msgid "这里的滤波器就是一个 :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>`。如果只想影响某一次播放，不要加到总线上；去控制那一次播放返回的 :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` 会更合适。"
msgstr ""
"The filter here is a :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>`. If you only want to affect one playback instance, do not add it to the bus; controlling the returned :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` is a better fit."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:196
#: c89ebbb98f3b4eea89e5d91a601ef35b
msgid "淡入淡出"
msgstr "Fade In and Fade Out"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:198
#: 8224c2259ff14f84859a4e5624057deb
msgid "总线对象不是 Godot 节点，不能直接用 ``tween_property()`` 绑属性动画。可以用一个循环逐帧插值："
msgstr ""
"Bus objects are not Godot nodes, so you cannot bind property animation with ``tween_property()`` directly. You can interpolate frame by frame in a loop:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:200
#: 6dbdc0ef7ce84a1a9130057de30cad77
msgid ""
"func fade_bus(bus_name: String, target_db: float, duration: float):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(bus_name)\n"
"    if bus == null:\n"
"        return\n"
"\n"
"    var start_db := bus.get_volume_db()\n"
"    var elapsed := 0.0\n"
"\n"
"    while elapsed < duration:\n"
"        await get_tree().process_frame\n"
"        elapsed += get_process_delta_time()\n"
"\n"
"        var t := clampf(elapsed / duration, 0.0, 1.0)\n"
"        bus.set_volume_db(lerpf(start_db, target_db, t))\n"
"\n"
"    bus.set_volume_db(target_db)"
msgstr ""
"func fade_bus(bus_name: String, target_db: float, duration: float):\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(bus_name)\n"
"    if bus == null:\n"
"        return\n"
"\n"
"    var start_db := bus.get_volume_db()\n"
"    var elapsed := 0.0\n"
"\n"
"    while elapsed < duration:\n"
"        await get_tree().process_frame\n"
"        elapsed += get_process_delta_time()\n"
"\n"
"        var t := clampf(elapsed / duration, 0.0, 1.0)\n"
"        bus.set_volume_db(lerpf(start_db, target_db, t))\n"
"\n"
"    bus.set_volume_db(target_db)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:220
#: 38f0155fe03b4b3d965d76b96558fd4e
msgid "常见用法是暂停时压低音乐："
msgstr "A common use is lowering music while paused:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:222
#: 4f9cd9d6ac104ac4864951cbad20eba0
msgid ""
"func on_pause_changed(paused: bool):\n"
"    if paused:\n"
"        fade_bus(\"Music\", -10.0, 0.25)\n"
"    else:\n"
"        fade_bus(\"Music\", 0.0, 0.25)"
msgstr ""
"func on_pause_changed(paused: bool):\n"
"    if paused:\n"
"        fade_bus(\"Music\", -10.0, 0.25)\n"
"    else:\n"
"        fade_bus(\"Music\", 0.0, 0.25)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:231
#: c5414990ae65459ea69fdb5fb99e73dd
msgid "降低音乐给对白让位"
msgstr "Lower Music to Make Room for Dialogue"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:233
#: de7d12476f544c849a610141319cdb7c
msgid "这个效果常被叫作 ducking，意思是对白播放时先把音乐压低，播放结束后再恢复。"
msgstr "This effect is often called ducking: lower the music while dialogue plays, then restore it afterward."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:235
#: 175124bd6f224415a32593280ad49aa3
msgid ""
"var normal_music_db := 0.0\n"
"var ducked_music_db := -12.0\n"
"\n"
"func play_voice_line(path: String):\n"
"    await fade_bus(\"Music\", ducked_music_db, 0.2)\n"
"\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var voice_bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Voice\")\n"
"    var sound := system.create_sound_from_file(path)\n"
"    var channel := system.play_sound(sound, voice_bus, false)\n"
"\n"
"    while channel != null and channel.is_playing():\n"
"        await get_tree().process_frame\n"
"\n"
"    await fade_bus(\"Music\", normal_music_db, 0.3)"
msgstr ""
"var normal_music_db := 0.0\n"
"var ducked_music_db := -12.0\n"
"\n"
"func play_voice_line(path: String):\n"
"    await fade_bus(\"Music\", ducked_music_db, 0.2)\n"
"\n"
"    var system := FmodServer.main_system\n"
"    var voice_bus := system.get_channel_group_by_name(\"Voice\")\n"
"    var sound := system.create_sound_from_file(path)\n"
"    var channel := system.play_sound(sound, voice_bus, false)\n"
"\n"
"    while channel != null and channel.is_playing():\n"
"        await get_tree().process_frame\n"
"\n"
"    await fade_bus(\"Music\", normal_music_db, 0.3)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:253
#: f39170fc1ab549c2b527eb376b549a5e
msgid "这不是必须使用压缩器才能完成。对多数游戏来说，直接调低音乐总线已经足够清楚，也更容易理解和调试。"
msgstr ""
"You do not have to use a compressor for this. For most games, directly lowering the music bus is clear enough and easier to understand and debug."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:256
#: 44db81f71ccf4f7ab25c3b6f31983cfc
msgid "高级：混音矩阵什么时候需要看"
msgstr "Advanced: When to Look at the Mix Matrix"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:258
#: dfc8f90f94b3496eac293ae08318ecef
msgid ""
":ref:`Mix Matrix<glossary-mix-matrix>` 可以精确控制“哪个输入声道送到哪个输出声道”。如果你只是想让声音偏左或偏右，优先用 :ref:`FmodChannelControl.set_pan()<FmodChannelControl-set_pan>`。"
msgstr ""
"A :ref:`Mix Matrix<glossary-mix-matrix>` precisely controls which input channel is sent to which output channel. If you only want to move a sound left or right, prefer :ref:`FmodChannelControl.set_pan()<FmodChannelControl-set_pan>`."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:260
#: 2dad829f93b644dea0dfd5a2ac21ca6c
msgid "只有在这些情况下，才建议继续研究 :ref:`FmodChannelControl.set_mix_matrix()<FmodChannelControl-set_mix_matrix>`："
msgstr "Continue to :ref:`FmodChannelControl.set_mix_matrix()<FmodChannelControl-set_mix_matrix>` only in cases like these:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:262
#: 34f62650be9c41d5a632ad6f1abec955
msgid "要把单声道手动分配到多声道输出，也就是 :ref:`Upmix<glossary-upmix>`。"
msgstr "You need to manually distribute mono audio to multi-channel output, which is :ref:`Upmix<glossary-upmix>`."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:263
#: b9af6542a28848ae945ee7e699bce360
msgid "要把 5.1 等多声道内容折叠成立体声，也就是 :ref:`Downmix<glossary-downmix>`。"
msgstr "You need to fold multi-channel content such as 5.1 down to stereo, which is :ref:`Downmix<glossary-downmix>`."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:264
#: 98797f4e7b9f4391992c937720697668
msgid "要交换左右声道或做特殊声道路由。"
msgstr "You need to swap left and right channels or do special channel routing."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:265
#: ce9e27af392f495a8ab2dd5bf6003d3b
msgid "要调试某个音频资产的声道顺序。"
msgstr "You need to debug the channel order of an audio asset."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:267
#: 4e2fac3e834a4a49876f4f4794a4ffb0
msgid "一个最小示例：把立体声左右声道对调。"
msgstr "A minimal example: swap the left and right channels of a stereo sound."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:269
#: 467d8678725a4a5f9e55f6f1cb350ce6
msgid ""
"func swap_stereo(channel: FmodChannel):\n"
"    var matrix := PackedFloat32Array([\n"
"        0.0, 1.0,\n"
"        1.0, 0.0,\n"
"    ])\n"
"\n"
"    channel.set_mix_matrix(matrix, 2, 2)"
msgstr ""
"func swap_stereo(channel: FmodChannel):\n"
"    var matrix := PackedFloat32Array([\n"
"        0.0, 1.0,\n"
"        1.0, 0.0,\n"
"    ])\n"
"\n"
"    channel.set_mix_matrix(matrix, 2, 2)"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:280
#: d487fff1174a4d3788d84ea0c2d6f85f
msgid "性能与排查"
msgstr "Performance and Troubleshooting"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:282
#: 61725647995848198ee04446818c538d
msgid "混音相关问题可以从三处开始看："
msgstr "For mixing-related issues, start with these three checks:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:284
#: ddd7c1b5b0bf42cdad70a7c7a86c2875
msgid "声音是否被送到了正确的 :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>`。"
msgstr "Whether the sound is routed to the correct :ref:`Bus<glossary-bus>`."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:285
#: ec663aba92ff43058c65cbf7cca2de5b
msgid "目标总线是否被静音、独奏或音量过低。"
msgstr "Whether the target bus is muted, soloed, or too quiet."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:286
#: eaadb8d2a1474d1aa222e4b1354b8fc1
msgid "是否有过多 :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` 同时启用。"
msgstr "Whether too many :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` effects are enabled at the same time."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:288
#: 9314359c7ad14c0bb78db20e722c067c
msgid "可以在 Godot 性能监视器中查看 FMOD 注册的性能项："
msgstr "You can view FMOD's registered performance metrics in Godot's performance monitors:"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:290
#: 1b04d1ec80bb47658d7208089768c655
msgid ""
"func _process(_delta):\n"
"    var dsp_usage = Performance.get_monitor(\"FmodCPUUsage/DSP\")\n"
"    var stream_usage = Performance.get_monitor(\"FmodCPUUsage/Stream\")\n"
"    var channels = FmodServer.main_system.get_channels_playing()\n"
"\n"
"    print(\"DSP: %.2f%% | Stream: %.2f%% | Real: %d | Virtual: %d\" % [\n"
"        dsp_usage,\n"
"        stream_usage,\n"
"        channels[\"real\"],\n"
"        channels[\"virtual\"],\n"
"    ])"
msgstr ""
"func _process(_delta):\n"
"    var dsp_usage = Performance.get_monitor(\"FmodCPUUsage/DSP\")\n"
"    var stream_usage = Performance.get_monitor(\"FmodCPUUsage/Stream\")\n"
"    var channels = FmodServer.main_system.get_channels_playing()\n"
"\n"
"    print(\"DSP: %.2f%% | Stream: %.2f%% | Real: %d | Virtual: %d\" % [\n"
"        dsp_usage,\n"
"        stream_usage,\n"
"        channels[\"real\"],\n"
"        channels[\"virtual\"],\n"
"    ])"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:304
#: 070e3af31d7b4f59809a2a8146aa2426
msgid "这里的 ``Virtual`` 指 :ref:`Virtual Channel<glossary-virtual-channel>`。它不一定是错误，很多时候只是 FMOD 在帮你节省混音资源。"
msgstr ""
"Here, ``Virtual`` refers to :ref:`Virtual Channel<glossary-virtual-channel>`. It is not necessarily an error; often it simply means FMOD is saving mixing resources for you."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:307
#: 457ccfbc4f0f419eb66207be2bff55f2
msgid "建议"
msgstr "Recommendations"

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:309
#: 1bc5478a4f944caf93d93daf67d48b5f
msgid "先用 ``Master``、``Music``、``SFX``、``Voice``、``UI`` 这样的简单结构。"
msgstr "Start with a simple structure such as ``Master``, ``Music``, ``SFX``, ``Voice``, and ``UI``."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:310
#: b7984b6a49294bffba0b60b9df33609d
msgid "只有需要单独控制时才继续拆分总线。"
msgstr "Split buses further only when you need separate control."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:311
#: 96cad291a7a44273ad0ef86747e4f667
msgid "多个声音共享效果时，把 :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` 加到总线上。"
msgstr "When multiple sounds share an effect, add the :ref:`DSP<glossary-dsp>` to the bus."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:312
#: e3334a6288474f75b114526cd08d1f06
msgid "单个声音的临时控制，优先使用播放返回的 :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>`。"
msgstr "For temporary control of one sound, prefer the :ref:`Channel<glossary-channel>` returned by playback."

#: ../../source/user_guide/mixer.rst:313
#: 3725cb29fe3c45e8a695f1928af5fe15
msgid "不要一开始就设计很深的总线树；能听清、能维护，比“看起来专业”更重要。"
msgstr ""
"Do not design a very deep bus tree at the beginning. Being easy to hear and maintain matters more than looking professional."
